      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You use this method to optimize the rendering of your view in situations where you can represent your views contents entirely using a layer object. If your view’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsview/1483461-wantsupdatelayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the view calls this method instead of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsview/1483686-drawrect"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " during the view update cycle. Custom views can override this method and use it to modify the properties of the underlying layer object. Modifying layer properties is a much more efficient way to update your view than is redrawing its content each time something changes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you want to update the contents of your layer, mark the view as dirty by setting its "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsview/1483360-needsdisplay"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Doing so adds the view to the list of views that need to be refreshed during the next update cycle. During that update cycle, this method is called if the"
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsview/1483461-wantsupdatelayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property is still "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Your implementation of this method should not call "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "super"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
